metadata.name: Rebug #10
metadata.description:
A debug view of the underlying particulate algorithm of Atoms' Gaze and Quantum Folly. Refined as a gift for collectors.

Enjoy watching the structures form. Once it's fully rendered you can download a full resolution image of 3508 x 4961 px by ***double clicking/tapping***. At this size the piece is printable at A3 size at 300 dpi. If you're interested in acquiring a signed print please contact @KRANKARTA.

Created on Chrome desktop 103.0 on 2022-08-06 in javascript and GLSL. Results on other browsers/devices may vary.

metadata.name: Get Out of My Head #10
metadata.description:
'Get Out of My Head' is the first generative micro-blockbuster on fx(hash)! Mystery, suspense, a spectacular finale and many of the best parts of the coolest celebrities combined by an algorithm into a single artwork.

----------------------------
* Just click to play/pause the movie.
* Press [v] to on/off sound.
----------------------------

SUMMARY OF PREVIOUS EPISODES

By the beginning of the census campaign, it was not possible to meet Brity with a clear look - a black patch replaced at least one eye of each individual. Their thoughts, behavior, reasoning, attitude towards others, towards themselves, towards life — all this became dark in an instant! But Mr. Lived declared victory early. A small group of brave Brities opened up resistance, trying to beat this damn crap out of themselves!


PROJECT DETAILS

'Get Out of My Head' generative animated collection in its art component is the search for new solutions, transfer to the cinema territory and the development of the classic absurdist Dada collage; from a technical point of view, this project is an exploration of the p5.js' multimedia capabilities.

Coding the Animation
The animation prototype was made in After Effects, then the coordinates and angle of rotation changes for each element were exported to a data file. When playing a movie, the algorithm reads this data frame by frame and animates the scene.

Elements Library
The audiovisual library, from which the algorithm selects parts for the assembly of each movie, contains over 400 elements: 92 celebrity eyes, 63 noses, 78 mouths, 66 hairstyles, 5 body types (hereinafter within each type there are several options for elements), 12 bikini types, 7 weapon types, 9 badge types, 4 necklace types, 5 sound types and 4 different bangs.

Star Cast
See Features to find out which parts of which cool celebrities are featured in your movie!

Created and directed by @m5alien
